    "content": "{\n  \"narration\": \"A quiet determination settles over you as you voice your intent. Elder Mirna regards you with clear relief, her tension giving way to a flicker of hope. She nods gravely, her hands clasped atop the counter. \\\"I had no doubt you'd answer, Norn. The folk here--myself included--owe you more than we can say.\\\"\\n\\nShe takes a moment, then gently pushes the ledger toward you, its cover worn from years of use. \\\"Here is the last record from the morning Elen left. You'll see the supplies she took for her patrol. If you wish, you may take what you need from the shelf--within reason.\\\"\\n\\nMirna hesitates, then places the old bronze key beside the ledger. The faded raven sigil catches the morning light, casting a tiny shadow across the counter. \\\"This belonged to my family, long ago, when the keep still stood proud. Elen did not take it, but I believe now it may serve you better. If you intend to face what lies beyond the forest, take it with my blessing.\\\"\\n\\nA hush falls across the store as a few customers glance your way, sensing something momentous. The bronze key, the ledger, and the hope of a village rest before you.\\n\\nWhat will you do next, Norn? Examine the ledger for clues, take the key, gather supplies, or set out for the east trail?\",\n  \"actions\": [\n    {\n      \"action\": \"updateTime\",\n      \"parameters\": {\n        \"timeEstimate\": 2\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}"
